Money Stuff =0A See, when I was a corporate lawyer, many years ago, I thoug=
ht that big =0Acompanies wanted to be incorporated in Delaware. Most of the=
m were, a =0A=0A=0A <https://bloom.bg/4aWfluz> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomber=
g.com/click=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12540782&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615=
cf44233be620525&p=3D02062025>=0A=0A=0A=0ADelaware=0A=0ASee, when I was a co=
rporate lawyer, many years ago, I thought that big =0Acompanieswanted to be=
 incorporated in Delaware. Most of them were, and are, and =0ADelaware is i=
n the business of catering to them. =E2=80=9CCatering to corporations=E2=80=
=9D =0Ameans mostly catering to corporatemanagers, to founders and chief ex=
ecutive =0Aofficers and boards of directors and controlling shareholders, s=
ince they are =0Athe ones who make decisions about where the company will b=
e incorporated. So =0ADelaware offers an attractive package to managers.The=
 package is =0A<https://bloom.bg/4aOSTDw>, roughly:=0A=0A * Delaware lets m=
anagers do a lot of stuff. There is a =E2=80=9Cbusiness judgment =0Arule=E2=
=80=9D saying that, for the most part, courts will not second-guess manager=
s=E2=80=99 =0Adecisions. So you can run your business without worrying too =
