ld violate the known laws of physics.=E2=80=9D But if the amount of =0Acapi=
tal that he needs from you istwo hundred dollars, then you should be very, =
=0Avery skeptical, because that violates the known laws of economics. Not t=
o get=0Atoo Chicago on you =0A<https://www.chicagobooth.edu/review/beyond-l=
amppost-theory-economic-policy>, =0Abut if he really had a viable antigravi=
ty device, he would have gotten $200 =0Afrom someone other than you.=0A=0AH=
ere=E2=80=99s a Bloomberg Businessweek profile <https://bloom.bg/3ECiweF> o=
