decisions. So you can run your business without worrying too much that some=
 random shareholder will sue you and a court will order you to do something=
 else.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Delaware doesn=E2=80=99t let =
managers do=C2=A0<em>anything=C2=A0</em>they want. The managers have fiduci=
ary duties to shareholders; they have to treat their shareholders fairly an=
d put their interests first. If you do certain bad things, shareholders wil=
l sue you, and a court=C2=A0<em>will=C2=A0</em>order you to knock it off. T=
his is good! For you, as a manager, it helps you credibly promise to invest=
ors that they will be treated well, which makes their shares more valuable,=
 which makes them willing to invest in your company. If there was <em>no=C2=
=A0</em>oversight over your relationship with shareholders, you=E2=80=99d h=
ave a hard time raising money.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Delaw=
are is <em>predictable</em>. Delaware has lots of corporate-law cases, so t=
here are a lot of precedents saying what is and isn=E2=80=99t allowed.=C2=
=A0If you ask your lawyer if you=E2=80=99re allowed to do something, she ca=
n probably give you a pretty confident answer. Delaware has a specialized c=
ourt =E2=80=94=C2=A0the Court of Chancery =E2=80=94=C2=A0for corporate disp=
utes, with experienced judges who know a lot about corporate law. The chanc=
ery court moves quickly, so cases can be resolved quickly, and it doesn=E2=
=80=99t have jury trials, so you don=E2=80=99t have to worry about your mer=
ger being stopped by the unpredictable decision=C2=A0of some random laypeop=
le.</li> </ol> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of these three things, the thir=
