=80=99t rebalance=C2=A0<em>every=C2=A0</em>day. If 60/40 investors have a r=
ule like =E2=80=9Crebalance once a month, so that we start each month with =
a portfolio that is exactly 60/40, and otherwise only rebalance if our port=
folio is more than 62% stocks or less than 58% stocks,=E2=80=9D then you co=
uld trade against that rule. You buy stocks on the last day of the month, i=
f stocks have been down that month, and otherwise you buy stocks if stocks =
have been down a lot and the 60/40 portfolios are far out of balance.</p> <=
